1) What is Spring Boot?
      *   Spring Boot is an open-source Java framework used to 
          create a Micro Service. 
      *   Spring boot is developed by Pivotal Team, and it provides
          a faster way to set up and an easier, configure, 
          and run both simple and web-based applications. 
      *   It is a combination of Spring Framework and 
          Embedded Servers. 
      *   The main goal of Spring Boot is to reduce development, 
          unit test, and integration test time and in Spring Boot, 
          there is no requirement for XML configuration.

2) Spring-boot-Starter
      * spring-boot-starter is a core dependency in Spring Boot applications.
          It provides essential features like auto-configuration, logging 
          and YAML support.

          What it enables you to do Once added, you can:
              * Create REST controllers using @RestController
              * Handle HTTP requests with @GetMapping, @PostMapping, etc.
              * Automatically start a web server when you run your application
          EX :-
               <dependency>
                    <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
                    <artifactId>spring-boot-starter</artifactId>
               </dependency>
